) of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1901" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Padillothorax" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Padillothorax" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">Padillothorax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is unusual, known from only a few other genera (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thorell" authorityYear="1887" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Epocilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Epocilla" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">Epocilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Peckham &amp; Peckham" authorityYear="1894" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Padilla" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Padilla" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">Padilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, some marpissines). The thoracic window is also different from the pale area on the top of the thorax seen in other baviines (e.g., 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Pittosporaceae" genus="Bavia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bavia nessagyna" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nessagyna">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">Bavia nessagyna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in alcohol), where it is neither as pale nor does it extend so far posteriorly as in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1901" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Padillothorax" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Padillothorax" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">Padillothorax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1885" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Stagetillus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Stagetillus" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">Stagetillus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp., and 
<taxonomicName authority="Maddison, 2020" authorityName="Maddison" authorityYear="2020" class="Arachnida" family="Pittosporaceae" genus="Maripanthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Maripanthus draconis" order="Apiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="draconis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">Maripanthus draconis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have a pale thorax, but it is not framed by dark, as most of the thorax is pale. Palp is also distinctively simple: embolus narrow, pointing distally (i.e., appears erect in standard ventral view), fused to the tegulum, with no tegular fold covering its base as in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1877" class="Arachnida" family="Pittosporaceae" genus="Bavia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bavia" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">Bavia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and many 
<taxonomicName authority="Caleb &amp; Sankaran, 2019" authorityName="Caleb &amp; Sankaran" authorityYear="2019" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Indopadilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Indopadilla" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">Indopadilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Epigynal openings anterior with simple copulatory ducts proceeding posteriorly. Abdomen with distinct transverse bands. First legs distinctly the longest. Male endite with lobe or sharp corner, unlike 
<taxonomicName authority="Caleb &amp; Sankaran, 2019" authorityName="Caleb &amp; Sankaran" authorityYear="2019" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Indopadilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Indopadilla" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">Indopadilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(whose endite is rounded, without lobes or corners).
</paragraph>
